# Git Attributes — Line Endings + Binary File Handling
#
# What this does:
# 1. Normalizes line endings (LF) across Windows/Mac/Linux so you never
#    get merge conflicts caused by different operating systems
# 2. Marks secret file types (.pem, .key) as binary so git warns you
#    if you try to commit them (extra safety net beyond .gitignore)
# 3. Marks lock files as "generated" so GitHub collapses them in PR diffs
#    instead of showing 5,000 lines of auto-generated changes
#
# Why it matters: Without this, a Windows developer and a Mac developer
# editing the same file will create diffs on every single line — because
# Windows uses CRLF line endings and Mac/Linux use LF. This file prevents that.
#
# Docs: https://git-scm.com/docs/gitattributes

# Auto-detect text files and normalize line endings to LF on commit
* text=auto

# Force LF line endings for these file types (prevents CRLF issues)
# Why: Shell scripts with CRLF line endings break on Linux/Mac.
# YAML/JSON with mixed line endings cause confusing diffs.
*.sh text eol=lf
*.bash text eol=lf
*.yml text eol=lf
*.yaml text eol=lf
*.json text eol=lf
*.md text eol=lf
*.txt text eol=lf
*.editorconfig text eol=lf
Makefile text eol=lf

# Secret file types — mark as binary so git warns on changes
# Why: Even though .gitignore blocks these, marking them as binary adds
# a second layer of protection. If someone force-adds a .pem file, git
# will show a "binary file changed" warning instead of displaying the key.
*.pem binary
*.key binary
*.p12 binary
*.pfx binary
*.jks binary
*.keystore binary

# Lock files — mark as "generated" for GitHub's linguist
# Why: Lock files are auto-generated and can be thousands of lines long.
# Marking them as generated tells GitHub to collapse them in PR diffs,
# so reviewers see your actual code changes — not noise.
package-lock.json linguist-generated
pnpm-lock.yaml linguist-generated
yarn.lock linguist-generated
Cargo.lock linguist-generated
go.sum linguist-generated
poetry.lock linguist-generated

# Binary formats — tell git not to try text-diffing these
# Why: Without this, git may try to diff images or fonts as text,
# producing garbage output and potentially corrupting files on checkout.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.webp binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf binary
*.eot binary
*.pdf binary
*.zip binary
*.tar.gz binary
